-- LG Elec aims to raise 2007 air-con sales 18 pct
-- 
-- Mon Jan 15, 2007 10:45pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/01/16/us-lgelectronics-aircon-idUSSEO30678120070116

 

 SEOUL  (Reuters) - LG Electronics Inc. ( 066570.KS ), the world's biggest maker of home-use air conditioners, said on Tuesday it aimed to increase sales of the equipment by 18.4 percent to $4.5 billion in 2007. 

 LG sold 12.3 million air conditioners last year, worth $3.8 billion, slightly short of its initial 2006 target of $4 billion. Air conditioner sales have accounted for about 40 percent of LG's home appliance sales, which contributes about a quarter of the firm's total revenue. LG set this year's production target at 16 million units and plans to expand overseas production to 60 percent of the total, from 55 percent in 2006, the company said in a statement. LG, which competes with local rival Samsung Electronics Co. Ltd. ( 005930.KS ) in making televisions and mobile phones, faces a challenge from the won's  KRW=  strength. The home appliance business usually delivers the highest profit margins among its divisions, which include units for mobile phones, plasma TV screens and televisions. LG shares fell 1.3 percent to 53,300 won by 0255 GMT, lagging a 0.09 percent fall in the wider market  .KS11 .